description:
For the last three years guitarist and clinician Lee Ritenour has been extremely busy with the 6 String Theory Guitar Competition in which guitarists and musicians from all over the world compete for prizes and scholarships from major universities like The Berkley College of Music. Major sponsors of the competition are Concord Records, D'Addario Strings, Monster Cable, and Yamaha.

This year in addition to him running the competition, Lee also released one of his most ambitious projects, "Rhythm Sessions," which features some of his dear friends that he's worked, performed, and toured with for well over 40 years. What Lee decided to to do is assemble over 30 different rhythm musicians from all over the musical map, as well as feature three of last year's 6 String Theory Competition winners to play some of his original compositions as well as music by Nick Drake and Herbie Hancock. "Rhythm Sessions" features musical icons such as Dave Grusin, Chick Corea, George Duke, Patrice Rushen, Stanley Clarke, Marcus Miller, Kurt Elling and many more.

In a career that spans over four decades, Lee Ritenour has been one of the most requested session musicians playing on well over 3,000 records. He's backed some of legendary musical minds in the business including Al Jarreau, B.B. King, Aretha Franklin, Barbara Streisand, Bob James, Carly Simon, Bobby "Blue" Bland, Frank Sinatra, Harvey Mason, Herb Alpert, Johnny Mathis, Minnie Riperton, Natalie Cole, Neil Diamond, Patti Austin, Phil Perry, Quincy Jones, Sonny Rollins, Stanley Turrentine, Steely Dan, Pink Floyd, Will Downing, and endless others. Lee has also been a sidemen and composer of and on many television and film scores like "An Officer and a Gentleman," "American Flyers," "On Trick Pony," "Three Days of Condor," "Starsky and Hutch," and "Charlie's Angels."

Recently, Lee was one of the featured musicians that took part of the 30th Anniversary of GRP Records that took place at the Blue Note Jazz Club in New York City. Lee shared the stage with label co-founder and pianist/composer Dave Grusin, vocalist Diane Schuur, bassist John Patitucci, and drummer Will Kennedy of The Yellowjackets.

Lee is currently on tour in support of "Rhythm Sessions," For upcoming tour dates or to order the disc visit him on the web at www.leeritenour or www.concordmusicgroup.com. For more information or to register to compete Lee's 6 String Theory Competition, please visit their website at www.sixstringtheory.com.
